.SH NAME
bb-pr-view - View a pull request


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr view  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
View a pull request by numeric ID, pull request URL, or pull request comment URL. Comment URLs resolve to the parent pull request.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for view

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr view 1
  bb pr view 1 --json title,state,source,destination
  bb pr view https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1
  bb pr view https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/1#comment-15
.EE


